The paper proposes a convolutional neural network for the segmentation of histological images, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV). The network is designed to be accurate and robust, which involves machine learning techniques such as batch normalization and rectified linear units, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also mentions the efficiency and end-to-end training of the network, which suggests a possible interest in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the proposed method in pathology and clinical treatment, which could be related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
